Description: Perfect gigging guitar - looks & plays great but not mint. Best value in the RG series - Beautiful custom look with the quilted sapele top at a great price point. Better at this price than anything you'll get new. Made in Korea in the 2001-2003 timeframe of superior construction for Ibanez before they moved a lot of production to China. Sacrifices nothing in the playablility features: Lightning fast Wizard II neck, resonant basswood body, 24 Jumbo fret board, Edge-Pro II tremolo, super hot Ibanez pickups, 3-way switch, Volume and tone controls Great players condition, has a lot of light pick swirling and surface scratching from normal play over the years but no deep scratches or dings or chips into the paint. Even still has the plastic coating with inspection sticker on the electronics cavity cover. Guitar has been well played but not abused. Frets are still in great shape, only light wear down by the cowboy chords The only parts missing are two of the tuning pegs are missing their tiny plastic washers but still hold tune well, especially since this is a locking system. The tuners are ping types and can be inexpensively replaced if you desire. Trem arm is a replacement that has some pitting but works perfectly. Truly an exceptional shredder for the money. Hate to see it go but I just have too many guitars and a couple of them have to go this year. Will be packed securely in a guitar shipping box in a decent gig bag with the strings detuned so there's no tension on the neck.
Title: Ibanez RG320QS Rare & Exotic Red Quilted Sapele Top w/ gig bag - great value
ConditionDescription: Excellent used condition - has light pick swirling & surface scratching - no deep scratches or chips into the paint
